function dayOfYear = jdate(dateString)%Function dayOfYear = jdate(dateString)%  Compute the day number of the year, sometimes called the Julian date.%  dateString must be a format accepted by DATENUM?DATESTR (see below). %%    DATEFORM number   DATEFORM string         Example%       0             'dd-mmm-yyyy HH:MM:SS'   01-Mar-1995 15:45:17 %       1             'dd-mmm-yyyy'            01-Mar-1995  %       2             'mm/dd/yy'               03/01/95     %       3             'mmm'                    Mar          %       4             'm'                      M            %       5             'mm'                     3            %       6             'mm/dd'                  03/01        %       7             'dd'                     1            %       8             'ddd'                    Wed          %       9             'd'                      W            %      10             'yyyy'                   1995         %      11             'yy'                     95           %      12             'mmmyy'                  Mar95        %      13             'HH:MM:SS'               15:45:17     %      14             'HH:MM:SS PM'             3:45:17 PM  %      15             'HH:MM'                  15:45        %      16             'HH:MM PM'                3:45 PM     %      17             'QQ-YY'                  Q1-96        %      18             'QQ'                     Q1           dateNumber = datenum(dateString);dateVector = datevec(dateNumber);firstOfYear = datenum(dateVector(1), 1, 1);dayOfYear = dateNumber-firstOfYear;%  Note, if the first day should be 1, add 1 to dayOfYear%  This could be an input argument.%  If you have to deal with 2 digit years, make pivotYear an input argument.